cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper presents a novel inference algorithm for graphical models, which is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of optimization techniques and probabilistic models suggests that it could be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.IT (Information Theory). The focus on undirected graphs and pairwise probabilities suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
